                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d535">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Prince <persName type="from">Cantacuzène</persName> to Mr.
                            <persName type="to">Adee</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of Russia</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1893-02-20">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 20, 1893</hi>
                        </date>. (Received February 21.)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Sir</hi>: In reply to your note of February 16,
                    concerning the refusal of our consul-general in New York to visé the passport of
                    Mrs. (not Miss) Mannie Lerin, a naturalized citizen of the United States, I beg
                    to say that it appears from the information I just received from our
                    consul-general that the said Mrs. Lerin declared herself to be a Jewess.</p>
                <p>In the present circumstance Mr. Olarovsky acted according to the instructions of
                    his Government, interdicting to vise passports of foreign Jews, with the
                    exception of certain cases, under which Mrs. Lerin can not be placed.</p>
                <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cantacuzène</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
